                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d58">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/6876: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cunningham</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-02-18T16:00:00+08:00"
                            >February 18, 1935—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received February 19—10:35 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>73. Major General Kenji Doihara, well-known Japanese militarist arrived from
                    Japan on the 16th. He called yesterday upon Mayor Wu Te-chen and General Huang
                    Fu, chairman of the political affairs readjustment committee of Peiping. He is
                    quoted in the press as emphasizing that all anti-Japanese activities in China
                    must be discontinued before a Sino-Japanese agreement can be reached. Repeated
                    to Legation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cunningham</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
